Takehazuchi no Kami appears in the ''{{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft}}'' under the name {{ill|Takehatsuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|建葉槌命|1=Takehazuchi|2=ja|3=天羽槌雄神|4=zh|5=天羽槌雄神|6=fr|7=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi-no-Mikoto|12=draft}}. She is said to have '''subjugated the star deity''' '''{{ill|Amanomikaboshi|ja|天津甕星|12=draft}} (also known as Kagaseo no Kami)''', whom '''{{ill|Takemikazuchi-no-Kami|ja|武甕槌命|12=draft}}''' and '''{{ill|Futsunushi-no-Kami|ja|経津主神|12=draft}}''' were unable to pacify.<ref>{{Cite book|和書|author=植松安|date=1920-06|title=仮名日本書紀|volume=上巻|pages=87–88|publisher=大同館書店|url={{NDLDC|961006/117}} |doi=10.11501/961006 }} ({{ill|National Diet Library Digital Collections|ja|国立国会図書館デジタルコレクション|12=draft}})</ref>

